    <section class="card" id="recap">
      <h2>Quick recap: Chapters 6–12</h2>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div>
          <p><strong>At the cabin</strong>, Ben feels unsafe and hates the bush. Ray expects him to “man up”. The cabin is mouldy and gross. Ray hides a mysterious bag in the roof.</p>
          <p><strong>Ben & Olive</strong> start to team up. They explore the creek, build a small raft, and share secrets. Olive turns 8 and shows courage (but also argues when things feel wrong).</p>
          <p><strong>Family tension</strong>: Ray buys presents and a diamond ring for April after a campfire, and for a moment everyone is happy — but the lies are still there.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p><strong>Secrets & spying</strong>: Ben suspects the money is stolen. He listens in on April and Ray, writes notes, and decides to find the truth like a detective.</p>
          <p><strong>Hunting & fear</strong>: Ray hunts a rabbit. Ben feels sick about it and more scared of his dad. He also can’t swim but still tests the raft.</p>
          <p><strong>Plans to run</strong>: Ben hears talk of “papers” and maybe passports. He wonders if his parents have basically kidnapped him and Olive.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

